from collections import Counter

def fibonacci_digit_counts(n):
    (a, b) = (1, 1)
    for _ in range(n):
        (a, b) = (b, a + b)
    digit_counts = Counter(str(a))
    result = sorted(((count, int(digit)) for (digit, count) in digit_counts.items()), reverse=True)
    return result
